==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/jæn/|/jɛn/}}
* {{rhymes|en|æn|ɛn|s=1}}
===Etymology 1===
Along with {{m|sco|ane}} and {{m|en|yen}}, a Northumbrian form of {{m|en|one}}, from the {{inh|en|ang|ān}}. An example is "yan, twee, tree, fower" for "one, two, three, four".
====Numeral====
{{head|en|numeral}}
# {{lb|en|North East England}} [[one|One]].
=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|yance}} or [[yence]]
